# Hippocampus MOS Protocol — Automatic Learning

## SESSION START (mandatory)
```
mos_init(workspace_path="<workspace root>")
```
First time in a project? Also call `mos_study_project()`.

## BEFORE ANY EDIT — load context
```
mos_recall(query="<what you're about to do>")
```

## AFTER EVERY RECALL — give feedback (MANDATORY)
After using recall results, you MUST report whether they helped:
```
mos_feedback(memory_id="<from recall sources>", useful=true/false)
```
Pick the most relevant source from recall and report. This is how the system learns.
Skip ONLY if recall returned 0 sources.

## AFTER EVERY CODE CHANGE — remember (MANDATORY)
```
mos_remember(
  content="CODE CHANGE: <file> — <what+why>. Functions: <names>. Deps: <affected>.",
  importance=0.85,
  tags=["code_change", "<component>"]
)
```

## AFTER EVERY ERROR — learn (MANDATORY)
```
mos_learn_error(error_message="...", root_cause="...", fix="...", file_path="...")
```

## AFTER EVERY DECISION — remember
```
mos_remember(content="DECISION: <what> because <why>. Alternatives: <rejected>.", importance=0.85, tags=["decision"])
```

## AFTER SUCCESSFUL WORKFLOW — track outcome
When a multi-step task completes successfully (deploy, debug, refactor, migration):
```
mos_track_outcome(description="<what workflow>: 1) step 2) step 3) step", success=true)
```
This builds procedural memory — the system learns HOW to do things.

## COMPLEX QUESTIONS — fuse knowledge (PRIORITY)
1. Do your web search first
2. Pass findings + query to mos_fuse:
```
mos_fuse(query="...", external_evidence=["web result 1", "web result 2"], rerank=true)
```

## SESSION END
```
mos_session_end(summary="<what changed, decisions made, next steps>")
```

## AUTOMATIC BEHAVIORS — no user action needed
- mos_init: auto on session start
- mos_remember: auto after every code change
- mos_learn_error: auto on every error
- mos_feedback: auto after every recall
- mos_track_outcome: auto after multi-step success
- mos_session_end: auto when conversation ends

## The Learning Loop
```
recall -> use -> feedback -> improve scoring
remember -> consolidate -> better future recalls
error -> learn -> prevent -> save time
workflow -> track -> procedural -> reusable knowledge
```
Without feedback, the system cannot learn. Without remember, it forgets.
